# C Style Guide

## Standard and Compiler Flags
- C11 (`-std=c11`)
- Always compile with: `-Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic -Wshadow -Wstrict-prototypes -fstack-protector-strong`
- Debug builds add: `-fsanitize=address,undefined`
- Never suppress warnings with pragmas; fix the root cause

## Naming Conventions

```c
// Types: snake_case with _t suffix
typedef struct nr_ctx nr_ctx_t;
typedef enum { NR_OK = 0, NR_ERR_TLS = -1 } nr_error_t;

// Functions: module_verb_noun
nr_error_t nr_tls_init_ctx(nr_ctx_t *ctx);
int        buffer_event_insert(buffer_t *buf, const char *topic, const uint8_t *data, size_t len);

// Constants/macros: SCREAMING_SNAKE with module prefix
#define NR_MAX_TOPIC_LEN   256
#define NR_DEFAULT_PORT    8883

// Private (file-scope) functions: static, no module prefix needed
static int load_ca_cert(SSL_CTX *ssl_ctx, const char *pem);
```

## Module Prefixes
| Module | Prefix |
|--------|--------|
| nirantara-net public | `nr_` |
| nirantara-net internal | `nr_` |
| edge buffer | `buffer_` |
| edge sync | `sync_` |
| edge subscriber | `sub_` |

## Error Handling

```c
// ALWAYS check return values — no silent failures
SSL_CTX *ctx = SSL_CTX_new(TLS_client_method());
if (!ctx) {
    nr__log_ssl_error("SSL_CTX_new");
    return NR_ERR_TLS;
}

// Cleanup on error: use goto for multi-resource functions
nr_error_t nr_tls_init_ctx(nr_ctx_t *ctx) {
    SSL_CTX *ssl_ctx = NULL;
    X509    *ca      = NULL;
    BIO     *bio     = NULL;
    nr_error_t rc    = NR_ERR_TLS;

    ssl_ctx = SSL_CTX_new(TLS_client_method());
    if (!ssl_ctx) goto out;

    bio = BIO_new_mem_buf(ctx->cfg.ca_cert_pem, -1);
    if (!bio) goto out;

    ca = PEM_read_bio_X509(bio, NULL, NULL, NULL);
    if (!ca) goto out;

    /* ... success path ... */
    rc = NR_OK;

out:
    if (bio) BIO_free(bio);
    if (ca)  X509_free(ca);
    if (rc != NR_OK && ssl_ctx) { SSL_CTX_free(ssl_ctx); ssl_ctx = NULL; }
    ctx->ssl_ctx = ssl_ctx;
    return rc;
}
```

## Memory Discipline
- Every `malloc` is checked immediately; on NULL return `NR_ERR_MEM`
- Matching free in the same scope level where possible
- Use `goto out` pattern for multi-allocation functions (no nested ifs)
- Zero sensitive memory before freeing: `OPENSSL_cleanse(key_buf, len)`
- No `realloc` without capturing return in a temp pointer first

## Threading
- Use `_Atomic` (C11 stdatomic) for flags shared between threads
- Mutexes: `pthread_mutex_t`, always `pthread_mutex_destroy` in cleanup
- Never hold a mutex across a blocking I/O call
- The sync thread accesses SQLite via a **separate** db connection (WAL mode allows this)

## Structs and Headers

```c
// Public header: opaque pointer only — never expose internals
typedef struct nr_ctx nr_ctx_t;   // in net.h

// Internal header: full definition
struct nr_ctx {                    // in internal.h
    nr_config_t      cfg;
    SSL_CTX         *ssl_ctx;
    struct mosquitto *mosq;
    EVP_PKEY        *keypair;
    /* ... */
};
```

## Logging
Use the internal `NR_LOG` macro — never `printf` in library code:

```c
NR_LOG_INFO("mqtt: connected to %s:%d", ctx->cfg.server_ip, ctx->cfg.mqtt_port);
NR_LOG_ERR("tls: %s", ERR_reason_error_string(ERR_get_error()));
```

## What NOT to Do
- No `strncpy` (use `strlcpy` or manual + null-terminate)
- No VLAs (variable-length arrays) — fixed max sizes or heap
- No global mutable state outside of the `nr_ctx_t` / `buffer_t` structs
- No `exit()` inside library code — return error codes up the stack
- No `assert()` in production paths — use explicit checks and return codes
